{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d56e9550-97d8-41c1-a747-8a14c8e76865","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` but is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_6cglpIob18kJOsVHL45glh","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d8543d812a094c88951768f799e9d783/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-d8543d812a094c88951768f799e9d783/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"b6d586a2-dda2-46dd-869c-6b40b0829933","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters. Files can only reference modules/types defined in files that are listed *before* them in the `.fsproj` file.\n\nCurrently, the `.fsproj` has:\n1. `Services.fs` - depends on `Domain.fs` (opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` - defines the domain types\n3. `Program.fs` - depends on both `Domain.fs` and `Services.fs`\n\nThe problem is that `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` uses types from `Domain.fs`. Similarly, `Program.fs` needs both `Domain.fs` and `Services.fs` before it.\n\n\nThe fix is straightforward: I need to reorder the files so `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, and finally `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":500,"requestId":"190E:142AE8:12D7533:15376C7:6A066F0B"},"id":"14bff7fc-5cf1-4abd-bdff-53cb3925c6e8","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:55:48.070Z","parentId":"189d2491-e88d-48c2-b7c0-603e9af3e831"}
